author: Scary Pockets
description:
Hallllllo Pockets fans. Wanted to share a live performance of a song off my new solo record with you all. It may not be the funk you've come to expect here but maybe you'll like it anyway!

You can hear the whole album here:
https://open.spotify.com/album/3nOzS0itdydKWDI1CJjf6G?si=cUZwiFgCTu2Zi-fGYjRCWA

Thanks for watching!

Ryan

"Missing Girl"
written by Ryan Lerman, Tamir Barzilay & Jesse Singer

There’s a missing girl lying next to me
A smoke alarm low battery
If I only knew the way to your heart


New fake earthquake miss-take it all out on me
Guess I'm no fun, high strung, how dare I leave
Breath wrong eat wrong don't hold me hand when we walk

Pull the carpet up theres wood below
Its good old wood, theres bloodstains though
If I only knew the weight of your

Love me hate me break me to make me come back
Guess I’m heartless a narcissist psycho in fact
No jokes, no songs, don’t hold my hand when we walk

Ryan Lerman - Guitar, Vocals
Beatrix - Glockenspiel, Bgvs
Tamir Barzilay -
title: RYAN LERMAN // Missing Girl (Live)
